    header
      h1 Gulpy pages
      .subtitle A small recipe to start using beautiful languages like&#32;
        a.text-warning(href='http://coffeescript.org') CoffeeScript
        | ,&#32;
        a.text-success(href='http://jade-lang.org') Jade
        |  and&#32;
        a.text-info(href='http://lesscss.org')  LESS
        |  and publishing it on&#32;
        a.text-danger(href='http://pages.github.com')  GitHub pages
        | .

    .container
      .row.text-center
        .col-lg-4
          i.text-danger.fa.fa-github.fa-5x
          h2.text-danger Clone
          p
            pre git clone git@github.com:davinov/gulpy-pages.git [name-of-your-project]
          p Create your GitHub repo and change the original remote
            pre git remote set-url origin [your-github-repo-url]
          p Install npm / node then gulp
            pre [sudo] npm install -g gulp
            pre npm install

        .col-lg-4
          i.text-success.fa.fa-code.fa-5x
          h2.text-success Develop
          p Modify files in app folder and compile then with
            pre gulp build
          p Or watch for changes in your code with
            pre gulp watch
          p Install dependencies using bower or directly add them in vendor folder

        .col-lg-4.color-3
          i.text-info.fa.fa-globe.fa-5x
          h2.text-info Publish
          p Init the gh-pages branch in your public directory
            pre.
              cd public
              git init
              git branch --orphan gh-pages
              git remote add origin [your-github-repo-url]
              cd ..
          p Compile, minify, commit your changes in public folder then push them on gh-pages branch
            pre ./publish.sh

    .container
      .row.text-center
        .col-lg-4
          a.btn.btn-danger(href='https://github.com/davinov/gulpy-pages') Go to GitHub repo »
        .col-lg-4
          a.btn.btn-success(href='http://localhost:3000') See your site live at localhost:3000 »
        .col-lg-4
          a.btn.btn-info(href='#') See your site published »

    footer
      :markdown
        Made an afternoon I was tired of [brunch](http://brunch.io) and tried [gulp](http://gulpjs.com) instead.
        [@davinov](http://david.nowinsky.net)


